{"lastModified":1740552768720,"uri":"c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Base / Home Port: Cairns, Queensland, Australia\nOperating Area: Australia\n\nMoored in Cairns, Queensland, M.Y. Beluga is an explorer-style motor yacht custom-built by Moonen in 2006 and last refitted in 2024. She was built as a go-anywhere yacht with 4,000 nm range, a robust elegant style, a wide beam, and therefore unusually large volume for her length. M.Y. Beluga is available for international charters.\n\nAn expansive 35 metres in length, M.Y. Beluga sleeps 10-12 guests in 5 staterooms, including a master suite, two double cabins (with dividing wall, which creates two single beds in each cabin), two twin cabins and two Pullman beds. Timeless styling and beautiful furnishings create an elegant and comfortable atmosphere. Carrying several crew onboard to ensure a relaxed luxury yacht experience.\n\n","blueprint":{"name":"BELUGA","images":["/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::a23daab0-f40c-11ef-8248-8fd3f7475073/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::98732d80-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::987661d1-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::9876d700-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::9875c590-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::9875eca1-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.jpeg/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::1cd136c0-f40d-11ef-8113-77a8f8cb108e/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::70a3a620-f40d-11ef-ad68-870f375f1821/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::7753fd80-f40d-11ef-ad68-870f375f1821/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::848278b0-f40d-11ef-83ac-8bac6149c36b/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::8cf42f20-f40d-11ef-bb29-b5b227aef708/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::c0f7c430-f40d-11ef-840b-e5c1b5206d05/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::c4777510-f40d-11ef-840b-e5c1b5206d05/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::ca3b4990-f40d-11ef-8248-8fd3f7475073/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::ce1353a0-f40d-11ef-8248-8fd3f7475073/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::d4228900-f40d-11ef-9da1-3307fbc3033a/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::d918fb60-f40d-11ef-9036-e91b27fee8e5/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::dd679500-f40d-11ef-9036-e91b27fee8e5/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::ef907a30-f40d-11ef-a8e4-2b8582cd9593/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::32d1e270-f40e-11ef-8794-8b968ad357f0/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::9876aff0-e57a-11ee-8565-d741043754b1.png/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::392b1920-f40e-11ef-9036-e91b27fee8e5/{imageVariant}"],"make":"Moonen","model":"Moonen 114 Explorer","maxCrew":6,"sleeps":12,"builtYear":2006,"architect":"","interiorDesigner":"","refitYear":2024,"topSpeed":"","cruiseSpeed":10,"fuelCapacity":45180,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Master Cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"Double or Twin Cabins","value":"2"},{"label":"Twin Cabins and a pullman (bunk)","value":"2"}],"cabins":5,"bathrooms":"","decks":4,"length":34.7,"beam":7.9,"draft":2.3,"hullType":"","hullConstruction":"","tonnage":313,"superStructure":[],"engines":"Twin MTU 12V 2000 M60","amenities":[{"label":"Air Conditioning"},{"label":"Underway Stabilisers"},{"label":"Zero Speed Stabilisers"},{"label":"Alfresco Dining"},{"label":"Jacuzzi (6 person)"},{"label":"Sun Deck"},{"label":"Sun Beds","quantity":"4"},{"label":"Refrigerator"},{"label":"BBQ"},{"label":"Generators","quantity":"2"}],"toys":[{"label":"Stand-up Paddle Boards","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Scuba diving sets","quantity":"10"},{"label":"Snorkelling sets","quantity":"12"},{"label":"Seabobs F5","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Foam Floating Lilypad","quantity":"1"},{"label":"2 person Sea Biscuit","quantity":"1"},{"label":"Water Skis","quantity":"1"},{"label":"Knee board","quantity":"1"},{"label":"Inflatable and Towable Toys","quantity":""},{"label":"Reef Fishing Gear"},{"label":"Water Sports Protection Helmets"},{"label":"Impact Vests"}],"entertainment":["Sonos Speakers","Broadband VSAT Internet","Netflix","Kayo Streaming Services","32” Smart TV ","Samsung BlueRay DVD Player"],"tenders":["2 x 4.3m Swift Mirage RIB 60hp tender"]},"crew":[{"name":"Sam Aldred","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f9ffc760-2a04-11ef-a6e4-430e130c5b63.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Sam brings a wealth of knowledge and a positive energy to his leadership role onboard M/Y Beluga.\nLeaving Australia at just 17 years of age to pursue a career in yachting, Sam has since been travelling the world\nworking on yachts ranging in size from 25m – 85m gaining his qualifications in both his role as Captain and\nalso engineering. With both parents working as Captains on vessels in Australia, Sam’s life always revolved\naround the water, this is his true passion and first love. It gave him an insight into what the role of a Captain\nentails from an early age. Sam’s career started in the Mediterranean and since then he has travelled the\nwaters extensively gaining a wealth of knowledge of the local areas and the most exclusive anchorages. He\nhas a love for fishing, diving and all things water and is racing off to the closest golf course in his time off. With\nan emphasis on attention to detail and safety onboard, Sam and his crew are always attentive to the guests’\nneeds and aims to create a safe and unforgettable experience."},{"name":"Curtis","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::bbbd2ed0-e50c-11ee-a65d-3911bb58e174.png/{imageVariant}","role":"Chief Officer","bio":"Originally from Wales in the UK, Curtis moved to Australia when he was eight years old. As first mate on-board, Curtis ensures the smooth day-to-day operations of the vessel, organising and facilitating guest activities, as well as maintaining the ship’s exterior in impeccable condition.\n\nWith a meticulous eye for detail, a passion for nature, and a love of exploration and adventure, Curtis has over ten years of experience in the marine industry working as a PADI dive instructor in Indonesia and along the East Coast of Australia.\n\nCurtis is a qualified marine biologist and ecologist specialising in tropical reef species, with Coxswain, and Master V maritime certifications. Having previously served as the president of the JCU Dive Club, he has operated and directed SCUBA diving liveaboards along the Great Barrier Reef and managed and operated the marine and activities department on Orpheus Island Lodge.\n\nWhen he’s not onboard, you’ll find him freediving, fishing, sailing and rock climbing."},{"name":"Emily Jaye","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::3e368c20-2a05-11ef-a6e4-430e130c5b63.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Growing up in Sunny North Queensland, Australia, Emily always enjoyed the sun and the sea. She decided to\ngive up her job in banking back in 2011 and take on a completely different adventure in the yachting industry.\nJoining her first vessel in the Mediterranean as a deck/stew and gaining her Yachtmaster, she switched to\nan interior role, stayed focused and within a few years gained her first role as Chief Stewardess. Emily has\na passion for all things wine and has recently completed her WSET level 2. With a strong attention to detail,\nEmily loves to interact with the guests and ensure they always have everything they need to make their trip a\nmemorable one. She enjoys the comradery of working within a team who all have the same goal of making\nthe experience for the guests the best it possibly can be."},{"name":"Flynn","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::18227086393::vessel::d5cc4f2a-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::c51eea90-e50c-11ee-a65d-3911bb58e174.png/{imageVariant}","role":"Steward","bio":"Originally from the West Coast of Auckland, New Zealand, Flynn’s connection to the maritime world runs deep, shaped by her parents’ involvement in a superyacht refit company instilled a life a sea for her from an early age. Flynn spent a year on a 60m luxury sailing yacht during its refit- rigging, interior and exterior. Back home, Flynn swum competitively for the Royal New Zealand Defense Force and worked as a barista before she made the move to Australia to work for Morris Nautical.\n\nIn her role as Stewardess, Flynn assumes a pivotal role in ensuring the seamless operation of the vessel. Flynn is in charge of provisioning, interior and housekeeping as well as delivering impeccable food and beverage service, consistently meeting the highest standards. Flynn’s unwavering dedication ensures that guests receive the utmost care and attention throughout their journey.\n\nWhen not on deck, Flynn loves to spend time sailing, hiking, doing yoga and exploring new places. She has a keen interest in photography and ocean conservation."}],"pricing":{"dayPricingFrom":{"currency":"AUD","price":3550000,"displayCurrency":"AUD","displayPrice":3550000,"unit":"DAY"},"dayPricingTo":{"currency":"AUD","price":12100000,"displayCurrency":"AUD","displayPrice":12100000,"unit":"DAY"},"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"AUD","price":14000000,"displayCurrency":"AUD","displayPrice":14000000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"AUD","price":14000000,"displayCurrency":"AUD","displayPrice":14000000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"DAY / 1 NIGHT CHARTER","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2025-12-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-12-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2027-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2027-12-31T23:59:59.999Z"}],"pricing":{"currency":"AUD","charterFee":3550000,"inputAmountTaxed":"EXCLUSIVE","note":"","unit":"DAY","lineItems":[{"item":"Charter Fee","quantity":1,"unitPrice":3550000,"amount":3550000,"taxRate":{"label":"GST","value":0.1},"conditions":"Daily"},{"item":"APA (non-commissionable)","conditions":"","quantity":0.25,"unitPrice":3905000,"amount":976250}],"total":4881250,"subTotal":4526250,"totalTax":355000},"inclusionZones":[{"label":"Australia","type":"Country","category":["Oceania","Australia and New Zealand","Australia"],"coordinates":[134.10701705798022,-25.516879284507734],"bbox":[112.908203125,-39.1455078125,153.61689453125,-10.0517578125]}],"exclusionZones":[],"petsAllowed":false},{"name":"2 NIGHT CHARTER","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2025-01-01T00:0